<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>116534</id>
    <title>Server adapter cannot find ModuleArtifact for a JSP if it is not selected in the Package Explorer</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Server adapter cannot find ModuleArtifact for a JSP if it is not selected in the
Package Explorer.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">If user select "Run -&gt; Run On Server" using menu bar, it is pretty easy to hit
this problem.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">I think Run On Server should take account of the current active editor page (for
example, the index.jsp is opened on a web application) and find a module
artifact for current editor page.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
